## What Is a 3 Carat Cushion Cut Diamond Ring?

A 3 carat cushion cut diamond ring centres a 3ct cushion-shaped diamond — approximately 9mm × 9mm in standard square proportions — in an engagement ring setting. At 3ct, the cushion cut moves from "noticeable" to "unmistakable." The face-up area at 3ct is approximately 81mm² versus 64mm² at 2ct — a 27% increase in visual surface. On the hand, a 3ct cushion reads differently from across a room, not just up close.

I'm **Farzana Hasan**, a GIA Expert. The [3 carat cushion cut](/cushion-cut-diamond) occupies a specific position in the diamond market: it is the minimum size at which The Crushed Ice Trap becomes consequential, the size at which natural diamond scarcity pricing becomes dramatic (the jump from 2ct to 3ct in natural GIA quality is steeper than any other carat weight step), and the size at which lab grown diamonds become the most financially rational choice by the widest margin.

What determines whether a 3ct cushion purchase succeeds or produces regret: understanding The Crushed Ice Trap (the trade-off between the modified brilliant's inclusion-hiding and its fire-hiding), understanding The Pillow Premium (why cushions cost more than princess at any size), and knowing that VS2 clarity at 3ct requires video verification in a way that VS2 at 2ct does not.

Full credentials and methodology at **[Diamond Critics](https://diamondcritics.com/about-farzana/)**.

