## 3ct Cushion Cut Diamond Clarity: VS2 vs SI1

Clarity grade selection at 3ct in a cushion modified brilliant is more consequential than at 2ct, and the advice that circulates online — "the modified brilliant hides inclusions, so buy SI1 and save money" — is The Crushed Ice Trap in action.

[![Cushion cut diamond solitaire engagement ring white gold pavé band](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/BrioPackshotBox/Rings/501590/501590_M1_CSH_DIM_wht_0100CT_W_Box5_001_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?ShapeID=Cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

**VS2 at 3ct cushion modified brilliant.** VS2 inclusions in a 3ct cushion modified brilliant are typically not visible to the naked eye under normal viewing conditions — the crushed ice pattern does scatter light around most VS2-grade inclusions effectively. However, "typically" is not "always." At 9mm face-up, a VS2 inclusion positioned near the table facet of a 3ct stone may be visible when the stone is viewed face-up in certain lighting. The correct approach to VS2 at 3ct: always request and review the HD 360° video from Blue Nile before purchasing, confirm you cannot see the inclusion at normal viewing distance, and do not rely on the clarity grade alone.

**SI1 at 3ct cushion modified brilliant.** SI1 at 3ct in a cushion modified brilliant is a meaningful risk. The inclusions in an SI1 stone are by definition larger than in a VS2 stone, and while the crushed ice pattern hides many of them, the 9mm face-up size at 3ct means there is more surface area for inclusions to be visible at oblique angles. SI1 cushions at 3ct can be eye-clean — video verification is essential — but the odds of visible inclusions are meaningfully higher than at VS2. The price savings between VS2 and SI1 at 3ct natural are $3,000–$6,000 — real savings that must be weighed against real risk.

**The clarity recommendation at 3ct natural:** VS2 with HD video confirmation is the practical minimum. VS1 eliminates the video-verification requirement. VVS2 and above is the correct choice for buyers who want zero clarity concern at 3ct face-up and can allocate the budget.

**The clarity recommendation at 3ct lab:** At $5,962 for GIA D-VVS1, the clarity compromise question does not arise. The lab cushion's price advantage makes VVS1 the entry grade — there is no financial reason to drop to VS2 or SI1 in the lab 3ct tier when D-VVS1 costs less than a natural SI1 at 3ct would.

